            "text": "3784 - وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "سَأَلَهُ جَمِيلٌ : عَمَّنِ اِشْتَرَى تِبْنَ بَيْدَرٍ كُلَّ كُرٍّ بِشَيْءٍ مَعْلُومٍ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "يَقْبِضُ اَلتِّبْنَ فَيَبِيعُهُ قَبْلَ أَنْ يَكْتَالَ اَلطَّعَامَ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فَقَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:3:2:21:13",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/13",
      "text": [
        " \"لاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3784 - Jamil asked Abu Abdillah (as) about a man who buys straw from a threshing floor, each load (kurr) for a specified price, and takes possession of the straw but sells it before measuring the grain.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in that.\""
        ]
      }
    },
